\begin_layout Subsection*
Pickling and Unpickling
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In some contexts,
 you'll hear about "Pickling." This is a high-performance form of marshalling used for distributed systems (like Spark or Akka).
 It serializes objects into a binary format.
 Because Scala 3 has a unified type system,
 "unpickling" a binary stream back into a typed object is safer than ever.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Summary:
 The Death of the Runtime Error
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Renaissance philosophy of reflection is simple:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Marshalling
\series default
:
 Should be derived,
 not manually written.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Reflection
\series default
:
 Should happen at compile-time via Mirrors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Metaprogramming
\series default
:
 Should be typed and quoted,
 never raw strings.
\end_layout

